description: Embryos that were cryopreserved during a specific fertility treatment cycle.

columns.name: RECORD_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier for the cycle record.

columns.name: LINE
columns.description: The line number for the information associated with this record. Multiple pieces of information can be associated with this record.

columns.name: CRYO_EMBRYO_ID_NAME
columns.description: A custom ID title for the cryopreservation. If not set, users will see a generated ID based on the line number, such as "Embryo N."

columns.name: CRYO_EMBRYO_DATE
columns.description: The date that the embryos were cryopreserved.

columns.name: CRYO_EMBRYO_DAY
columns.description: The number of days that an embryo has been in culture when it is cryopreserved.

columns.name: CRYO_EMBRYO_STAGE_C_NAME
columns.description:
The embryo's stage when it's cryopreserved.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries:

2 Cell


3 Cell


4 Cell

6 Cell


7 Cell


8 Cell


More than 8


Morula

Blastocyst

Unknown

columns.name: CRYO_EMBRYO_FERT_METHOD_C_NAME
